@NODE "AllocSoundMem()" "Sound: AllocSoundMem()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     AllocSoundMem()
Short:    Allocate memory for sample playback.
Synopsis: APTR AllocSoundMem(LONG Size [d0], LONG Flags [d1])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  allocates  a  block  of  memory  suitable for playing sound
samples.   It  is unlikely that the average developer will need to use this
function,  as  the  Sound  object  will handle audio memory when loading in
sample data.

All audio memory is formatted with 0's when allocated.

@{b}@{u}INPUTS@{uu}@{ub}
Size  - The Size of the memory to allocate.
Flags - Standard memory flags as outlined in AllocMemBlock().

@{b}RESULT@{ub}
Returns a pointer  to  the  allocated memory.  This function returns NULL
if an error occurs.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Kernel: @{"AllocMemBlock()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/AllocMemBlock()"}
        @{"FreeMemBlock()"  LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/FreeMemBlock()"}
Sound:  @{"FreeSoundMem()"  LINK "FreeSoundMem()"}

@EndNode
