@NODE "FreeSoundMem()" "Sound: FreeSoundMem()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     FreeSoundMem()
Short:    Frees a block of sound memory.
Synopsis: void FreeSoundMem(APTR MemBlock [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  frees  a block of sound memory.  For more details on memory
handling, see the kernel documentation on this subject.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
MemBlock
  Pointer to a MEM_SOUND memory block that was allocated from
  AllocSoundMem() or AllocMemBlock()

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Kernel: @{"AllocMemBlock()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/AllocMemBlock()"}
        @{"FreeMemBlock()"  LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/FreeMemBlock()"}
Sound:  @{"AllocSoundMem()" LINK "AllocSoundMem()"}

@EndNode
