@NODE "SetVolume()" "Sound: SetVolume()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     SetVolume()
Short:    Set the volume for a Sound.
Synopsis: LONG SetVolume(*Sound [a0], WORD Volume [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  will  set  the  volume for a Sound object.  If the Sound is
currently playing, then the volume will be altered as the sound plays.

The Sound->Volume field will be updated to reflect the new volume.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns the sound volume that was active before your new setting.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StopAudio()" "Sound: StopAudio()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StopAudio()
Short:    Stop all audio channels that are currently playing.
Synopsis: void StopAudio(void)

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  will  put  an immediate stop to all audio channels that are
currently playing sound data.  Note that if a Music object is playing, then
it will be stopped completely (you can restart it with Activate()).

@EndNode
